The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Truck kills 6-year-old
                                                                                                               Truck kills 6-year-old
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Rakhia Khatun, 6, a resident of Maukhali under Jagachha police station, was hit by a speeding truck and crushed under the wheels of another truck while crossing Kona Expressway near Garfa bridge at 10am on Monday. Both trucks sped away after the accident.        
	Local residents blocked the expressway to protest the mishap, holding up traffic for over an hour. They damaged a state bus, a private bus and a truck. Police intervened to bring the situation under control.                                                                                                                                                                           
